The paper discusses the end-to-end learning of representations of signals and images using energy-based models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically mentions the use of auto-encoders and CNNs, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision research. The case studies mentioned in the paper also involve time series and image data, which are relevant to the sub-categories of information theory and neural and evolutionary computing.
